{"TopicId":94043,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"SUGGESTION: Easy (and awesome) Visual Kerbal Specialization Scheme","CreatedByName":"jjansen","CreatedById":132945,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-12-21T22:01:44Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"jjansen","CreatedById":132945,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-12-21T22:01:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI can\u0027t at a glance tell my pilots from my engineers from my scientists.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETherefore I suggest the following:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EColorized uniforms\u003C/strong\u003E (\u00C3\u201A\u00C2\u00BF\u00C3\u201A\u00C2\u00A1SOUND FAMILIAR ANYONE?!)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#a52a2a;\u0022\u003ECrimson\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E or \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#daa520;\u0022\u003EGold\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E = Pilot\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#daa520;\u0022\u003EGold\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E or \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#a52a2a;\u0022\u003ECrimson\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E = Engineer\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#40e0d0;\u0022\u003ETurquoise\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E = Scientist\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETo be perfectly fair and to preempt the battle between \u0022certain\u0022 camps, there ought to be an option for the player to choose which scheme they want, or at least for the player to assign the colors they desire.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESplit-specialization Kerbals could adopt \u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#ff8c00;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOchre\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E, \u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#4b0082;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAmethyst\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E, or \u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#006400;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDartmouth\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E uniform schemes. Jacks of All Trades could adopt \u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#8b4513;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESienna\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E or \u003Cstrong\u003EJet\u003C/strong\u003E uniforms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFrankly, I can\u0027t understand why this wasn\u0027t implemented to begin with.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anquietas314","CreatedById":8761,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-12-21T22:07:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jjansen\u0022 data-cite=\u0022jjansen\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EColorized uniforms\u003C/strong\u003E (\u00C3\u201A\u00C2\u00BF\u00C3\u201A\u00C2\u00A1SOUND FAMILIAR ANYONE?!)\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#a52a2a;\u0022\u003ECrimson\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E or \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#daa520;\u0022\u003EGold\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E = Pilot\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#daa520;\u0022\u003EGold\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E or \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#a52a2a;\u0022\u003ECrimson\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E = Engineer\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#40e0d0;\u0022\u003ETurquoise\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E = Scientist\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBut, but... what about Jeb Bill and Bob\u0027s special orange uniforms?!?! Because they were the first (and best) astronauts in the game? D:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn a slightly more serious note, it\u0027d be a cool idea, provided those are left alone. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-12-21T22:29:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThey could have a small stripe on the helmet....\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ddenis","CreatedById":89784,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-12-21T23:03:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#FFA500;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERed\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E, \u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#0033ff;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Eyellow\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E, \u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#FF0000;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Eblue\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E. That\u0027s my colors. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E I mean... we can argue a lot about particular color choice.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EP.S. I\u0027ve already marked my kerbals with Texture Replacer\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222014-12-21T23:07:16Z\u0022 title=\u002212/21/2014 11:07  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 21, 2014\u003C/time\u003E by ddenis\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kegereneku","CreatedById":66154,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-12-21T23:12:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI would take \u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#0000FF;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlue\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E, \u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#D3D3D3;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWhite\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E, \u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#FF0000;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERed\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E for some patriotic reason...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMore seriously the color of the various real space suit have been picked for safety the various environment they are used.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMore info here.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.livescience.com/32618-why-are-astronauts-spacesuits-orange.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.livescience.com/32618-why-are-astronauts-spacesuits-orange.html\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHowever, since KSP only use one spacesuit it\u0027s not very important.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}